11/12/2015  by OctaStaff 
			in Private Financing News 












Share with your friendsYour NameYour EmailRecipient EmailEnter a MessageI read this article and found it very interesting, thought it might be interesting for you. The article is called Melody Special Situations Offshore Credit Fund  Filing. Terri Lecamp  Released Nov 12  Form D and is was published by Octafinance.com at http://www.octafinance.com/melody-special-situations-offshore-credit-fund-filing-terri-lecamp-released-nov-12-form-d/276762/.CaptchaSubmit
Melody Special Situations Offshore Credit Fund Form D
The New York-based Melody Special Situations Offshore Credit Fund, L.P. had published SEC form D about $156.30 million offering. The date of first sale was 2013-10-11. The raised $156.30 million. The offering is still open. The total offering amount was $156.30 million. The offering filing was filed on 2015-11-12. Melody Special Situations Offshore Credit Fund, L.P.’s clarification was: Customary management fees will be paid to Melody Capital Partners, LP, as described in the Issuer’s Confidential Private Placement Memorandum.. 
 Melody Special Situations Offshore Credit Fund is based in New York. The filler’s business is Pooled Investment Fund. The D form was signed by Terri Lecamp Treasurer of Melody Special Situations GP, LLC (Issuer’s GP). The company was incorporated in 2013. The filler’s address is: 717 Fifth Avenue, 12Th Floor, New York, Ny, New York, 10022. Terri Lecamp is the related person in the form and it has address: C/O Melody Capital Partners, Lp, 717 Fifth Avenue, 12Th Floor, New York, Ny, New York, 10022. Link to Melody Special Situations Offshore Credit Fund Filing: 000095014215002403.
Analysis of Melody Special Situations Offshore Credit Fund Offering
On average, firms in the Pooled Investment Fund sector, sell 37.80 % pooled investment fund interests. Melody Special Situations Offshore Credit Fund sold 100.00 % of the offering. The average investment floor size is $24.76 million for companies in the Pooled Investment Fund industry sector. The minimum investment for Melody Special Situations Offshore Credit Fund ‘s offering was $100000.

